GRANTCREATEEDITFORM.PURPOSECHARITYEVENTATTENDING: The IRS prohibits using donor-advised funds to pay for tickets to attend a charity event. However, you can recommend a grant to the charity in support of a specific event as long as you have paid the full cost to attend the event on your own.
GRANTCREATEEDITFORM.PURPOSECHARITYEVENTNOTATTENDING: The IRS prohibits to use a donor advised fund to pay for tickets to attend a charity event.
GRANTCREATEEDITFORM.PURPOSEMEMBERSHIP: The IRS prohibits using donor advised funds for memberships that are not 100% tax deductible.
GRANTCREATEEDITFORM.PURPOSENONBINDINGPLEDGE: Donor-advised funds can be used for a non-binding pledge. However, the IRS prohibits grants from a donor-advised fund from being used for a legally binding pledge.
GRANTCREATEEDITFORM.PURPOSEOTHER: Creating your own custom purpose may result in a longer approval process, as it may require us to consult with the charity to confirm the grant meets our program guidelines. Please enter your custom use below.
